        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Three ways to write a table in Podlite]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[In the article, Aliaksandr Zahatski investigates the capacities for grid creation inherent in the block-markup language Podlite. The article elaborates various specific syntax types—text mode that suits for performing quick note-taking, structure block format that is meant for cell-spanning arrangements and rich content, as well as data-driven integration for processing unformatted CSV or TSV files.]]></description>
            <pubDate>2026.07.15</pubDate>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.perl.com/article/three-ways-to-write-a-table-in-podlite/</guid>
            <link>https://www.perl.com/article/three-ways-to-write-a-table-in-podlite/</link>
            
            
            
            <author><![CDATA[aliaksandr_zahatski]]></author>
            
                
            
            
